01:13:57,397 --> 01:14:00,718
Report on snow day, school cancellation protocols.

990
01:14:03,197 --> 01:14:11,859
So the reason this is on your agenda is every year I get asked around this time, how do we decide when school closes and what can we do about it?

991
01:14:12,779 --> 01:14:15,339
Now, the main message is this.

992
01:14:16,499 --> 01:14:23,841
You should start planning now as a parent about a situation that might occur and who will help to cover your youngsters.

993
01:14:24,261 --> 01:14:29,762
If you have to go to work, who's going to stay at home, what neighbors can work with you.

994
01:14:30,700 --> 01:14:32,161
What situations can occur?

995
01:14:32,181 --> 01:14:38,064
Can you talk to your employers who may be coming in a little bit later on certain days to get things under control?

996
01:14:38,544 --> 01:14:40,385
You can't wait until the day it happens.

997
01:14:40,645 --> 01:14:41,926
You've got to start thinking about it.

998
01:14:42,466 --> 01:14:44,888
And oftentimes, we don't get

999
01:14:45,958 --> 01:14:49,541
a final call until later, because we don't know if the storm is going to hit.

1000
01:14:50,282 --> 01:14:53,765
You know, meteorologists do their job, but they can't be sure.

1001
01:14:54,565 --> 01:14:59,029
Sometimes the storm veers off at the last second, and sometimes it veers in at the last second.

1002
01:14:59,630 --> 01:15:00,711
And we need to be careful.

1003
01:15:00,771 --> 01:15:09,058
And sometimes the storm doesn't seem like it's coming to us at the beginning of school, but it's going to hit at 10 o'clock in the morning, and getting young people home is its own problem.

1004
01:15:09,861 --> 01:15:14,905
The other thing that we have to deal with is the fact that some youngsters have no one at home on a regular basis.

1005
01:15:15,685 --> 01:15:18,547
And getting them to school means they might get to eat a hot meal.

1006
01:15:19,228 --> 01:15:20,268
They have some supervision.

1007
01:15:21,529 --> 01:15:24,892
There's some other things going on that we want to provide.

1008
01:15:25,572 --> 01:15:31,316
On the other hand, if you really feel uptight and you really feel like maybe your child shouldn't be out, it's your option to keep them home.

1009
01:15:32,597 --> 01:15:36,500
Missing a day is not going to change the world as long as you're diligent about following up on the work.

1010
01:15:37,820 --> 01:15:39,020
We've got to understand these things.

1011
01:15:39,080 --> 01:15:40,541
Now, it takes a lot to figure this out.

1012
01:15:40,561 --> 01:15:41,721
We talk to the DPW.

1013
01:15:42,361 --> 01:15:44,322
We talk to the police department.

1014
01:15:44,362 --> 01:15:45,623
We talk to the fire department.

1015
01:15:45,683 --> 01:15:47,763
We talk to our own custodial crews.

1016
01:15:48,123 --> 01:15:50,544
We talk to the contractors who plow our schools.

1017
01:15:50,944 --> 01:15:51,925
We talk to neighbors.

1018
01:15:52,465 --> 01:15:53,285
What are they doing?

1019
01:15:53,345 --> 01:15:54,185
How are they doing it?

1020
01:15:55,066 --> 01:15:56,766
And some places are more challenging than others.

1021
01:15:57,226 --> 01:16:03,068
If you live in the narrow streets of Everett and Malden, it's a lot tougher to plow those streets than it is maybe in Medford.

1022
01:16:04,108 --> 01:16:05,709
It's a lot tougher to do certain things

1023
01:16:06,260 --> 01:16:13,162
and they have to make decisions a little bit earlier because they can't get their crews out as fast as our crews get out.

1024
01:16:15,162 --> 01:16:17,883
We want to provide intelligent days.

1025
01:16:18,163 --> 01:16:20,843
We also have to think about the days if teachers can't get there.

1026
01:16:21,344 --> 01:16:28,505
So school is open and the faculty can't make it in because they no longer all live in Medford or one community over.

1027
01:16:29,065 --> 01:16:30,786
People live in wider areas.

1028
01:16:31,406 --> 01:16:36,087
So to have a day where the faculty is missing doesn't give us a quality education day.

1029
01:16:36,922 --> 01:16:42,764
We started earlier this year, so that should help in terms of days, but you never know.

1030
01:16:43,524 --> 01:16:45,344
We've had years where there's been no school days.

1031
01:16:45,744 --> 01:16:48,545
We've had years when a couple years ago there was seven or eight school days.

1032
01:16:49,205 --> 01:16:50,126
And last year there were three.

1033
01:16:50,786 --> 01:16:51,746
So it's hard to know.

1034
01:16:51,846 --> 01:16:54,767
And one year we shut down schools when the buildings were too cold.

1035
01:16:55,967 --> 01:16:58,068
And it wasn't a question of snow, it just was too cold.

1036
01:16:58,908 --> 01:16:59,988
So there's a lot of reasons.

1037
01:17:00,849 --> 01:17:02,349
And we try to be upfront.

1038
01:17:02,389 --> 01:17:05,970
There's always somebody who tells me we shouldn't have done it, and there's somebody who always tells me we should have done it.

1039
01:17:06,723 --> 01:17:07,364
I mean, I guarantee you.

1040
01:17:07,384 --> 01:17:09,246
