1057
01:18:08,081 --> 01:18:12,523
So the learning has to be done in some classes by a specific date.

1058
01:18:13,045 --> 01:18:27,852
So I would really, really like to talk to you at some point about more online learning opportunities for our students and to have us present maybe to the state different ways for children to study from home.

1059
01:18:29,072 --> 01:18:32,754
That being said, Mr. Belson, you know how I feel.

1060
01:18:33,054 --> 01:18:41,918
I like to see our buildings open even for any kids that come, even if it's less teachers, even if it's anything because some kids don't have a warm house.

1061
01:18:42,455 --> 01:18:44,956
to stay in all day or parental supervision.

1062
01:18:45,396 --> 01:18:49,717
And some kids depend on our schools to have their breakfast and their lunch.

1063
01:18:50,117 --> 01:18:52,918
And they really shouldn't be home alone all that long.

1064
01:18:53,358 --> 01:19:03,861
So any opportunity that you can, I'm going to ask you to please try to keep some of our school buildings open for those families that really need us to be there for them on an everyday basis.

1065
01:19:04,481 --> 01:19:07,682
So that's how I feel, even though I hate driving in the snow.

1066
01:19:08,412 --> 01:19:08,832
understand.

1067
01:19:09,032 --> 01:19:10,293
Good luck making that call.

1068
01:19:10,353 --> 01:19:12,794
